<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,152,1538]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,1391,1417]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks</emphasis>
. The relationships of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[584,674,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sime">
<emphasis box="[584,674,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">E. sime</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear beyond inclusion within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1178,1340,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biuncinata">
<emphasis box="[1178,1340,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">E. biuncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. In the new species, the hind tibia bears two straight anterior subapical bristles of different lengths. So, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,240,1472,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sime">
<emphasis box="[151,240,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">E. sime</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to show an intermediate state of this character and is provisionally included in this species complex of the 
<taxonomicName box="[334,491,1512,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biuncinata">
<emphasis box="[334,491,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">E. biuncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
